# S05-T09: Nitro WebSocket Layer (crossws)

## Objective
One typed realtime channel for all agent/board/gate events (invariant §8).

## Execution
- Add a Nitro WS route (`server/routes/_ws.ts` via crossws/`defineWebSocketHandler`).
- Implement the event contract from T01: `epic.proposed|updated|accepted`, `board.created`,
  `gate.opened`, `task.created|moved`, `agent.activity`, `presence.sync`. Typed payloads in
  `shared/ws.ts`; a server `broadcast(event, payload)` helper used by T05/T07/T08.
- Rooms by `chatId`/`boardId` so clients subscribe to the scope they're viewing.
- Client composable `useRealtime()` reconnects and exposes a typed event stream.
- Confirm it runs under `bun --bun nuxt dev` (no Node-only deps); no Supabase realtime.

## Out
`server/routes/_ws.ts`, `shared/ws.ts`, `app/composables/useRealtime.ts`

## Done when
- Two browser tabs see each other's epic/task/gate events live with no refresh.
